---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../content/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Privacy Policy — ${site.name}`}
  description={`Privacy policy for ${site.name}, a live sports audio control app for iOS.`}
>
  <article class="section container prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      {site.name} is a live sports audio control app for iPhone and iPad. We are committed
      to protecting your privacy. This policy explains what information {site.name} collects,
      how it is used, and your choices.
    </p>

    <h2>Information You Provide</h2>
    <p>
      {site.name} does not require you to create an account. The app does not collect your name,
      email address, or other personal information unless you contact us directly for support.
    </p>

    <h2>Local Audio Files and Imported Content</h2>
    <p>
      Audio files you import into {site.name} remain on your device. {site.name} does not
      upload, transmit, or share your local audio files with any server or third party.
    </p>

    <h2>Spotify Integration</h2>
    <p>
      If you choose to connect Spotify, {site.name} uses the Spotify SDK and API to enable
      playback features. Your Spotify account information is handled by Spotify and is subject
      to <a href="https://www.spotify.com/legal/privacy-policy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Spotify's Privacy Policy</a>.
      {site.name} does not store your Spotify credentials.
    </p>

    <!-- TODO: Finalize this section based on actual analytics/crash reporting implementation -->
    <h2>Diagnostics and Crash Reporting</h2>
    <p>
      <!-- TODO: Update with specific details about crash reporting services used, if any -->
      {site.name} may collect anonymous crash reports and basic diagnostics to help improve
      app stability. This data does not include personally identifiable information.
    </p>

    <h2>Backup and Export Data</h2>
    <p>
      {site.name} offers backup and restore features that store data locally on your device
      or in your personal iCloud account. Backup data is not transmitted to our servers.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      {site.name} may integrate with the following third-party services:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Spotify (optional, for music playback)</li>
      <li>Apple (App Store, iCloud backup)</li>
      <!-- TODO: Add any additional third-party services -->
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each third-party service has its own privacy policy governing how your data is handled.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Since {site.name} stores data locally on your device, data retention is under your control.
      Deleting the app removes all locally stored data.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You can use {site.name} without connecting Spotify or any external service.</li>
      <li>You can delete your local data at any time by removing the app.</li>
      <li>You can manage iCloud backup through your device settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <!-- TODO: Replace with real support email -->
      If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact us at
      <a href={`mailto:${site.supportEmail}`}>{site.supportEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with
      an updated revision date.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .last-updated {
    font-size: var(--small);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
</style>
